1.Create account in Heroku website

2. Download Heroku CLI
Ubuntu:
# Run this from your terminal.
# The following will add our apt repository and install the CLI:
(https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs#introduction)
sudo add-apt-repository "deb https://cli-assets.heroku.com/branches/stable/apt ./"
curl -L https://cli-assets.heroku.com/apt/release.key | sudo apt-key add -
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install heroku

3. Login Heroku
$ heroku login

4. Clone simple setup project (NODEJS) in heroku 
github: https://github.com/nguyenthuyhanh0805/Simple_heroku_deploy.git

5. Create project in heroku
$ heroku create <name_project>

6. Push project in Git (Gitlab, Github)

7. Push project in Git of Heroku
$ git push heroku master

8. Open in the browser (with heroku host)
$ heroku open